WEBVTT

00:09.301 --> 00:11.762
[news jingle plays]

00:15.307 --> 00:16.350
Good evening.

00:16.391 --> 00:18.685
This is ABC's           
          World News Tonight.

00:18.727 --> 00:22.105
Frank Reynolds is sick tonight. 
         I'm David Brinkley.

00:22.147 --> 00:23.815
In Beirut, Lebanon, today

00:23.857 --> 00:24.691
a pickup truck

00:24.733 --> 00:26.026
loaded with explosives

00:26.068 --> 00:28.403
drove up              
      to the American embassy,

00:28.445 --> 00:30.364
and there was           
       a tremendous explosion

00:30.405 --> 00:31.823
during the lunch hour.

00:31.864 --> 00:36.703
Just after one o'clock,      
     maybe 1:05, I hear "Boom!"

00:36.745 --> 00:39.414
The loudest explosion       
      I'd ever heard in Beirut.

00:39.456 --> 00:40.707
[Peter Jennings]   The explosion

00:40.749 --> 00:42.667
at five minutes past 1:00     
            this afternoon

00:42.709 --> 00:44.002
devastated the embassy.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.379
At this late hour,

00:45.420 --> 00:47.214
we are told that more than     
          40 people are dead,

00:47.255 --> 00:48.882
between 80 and 100 wounded.

00:48.924 --> 00:51.551
Americans and Lebanese.

00:51.593 --> 00:53.178
[David Ignatius]   Run back     
            to the embassy,

00:53.220 --> 00:56.181
and the facade           
     of this beautiful embassy...

00:56.223 --> 00:57.974
I've described it         
            as being, like,

00:58.016 --> 00:59.726
looking at a human face

00:59.768 --> 01:02.020
that had had            
         the skin ripped away,

01:02.062 --> 01:05.023
so that you just saw        
           bones and blood.

01:05.065 --> 01:07.066
[Sam Wyman]   Oh,          
         it was wipeout time.

01:07.109 --> 01:08.902
It was terrible.

01:08.944 --> 01:10.570
I remember sitting         
      at my desk at headquarters,

01:10.612 --> 01:12.739
and somebody called me and said, 
     "Bob Ames has been killed.

01:12.780 --> 01:14.366
The embassy's been bombed."

01:14.408 --> 01:16.910
This criminal attack        
    on a diplomatic establishment

01:16.952 --> 01:19.871
will not deter us from our goals

01:19.913 --> 01:22.541
of peace in the region.

01:22.582 --> 01:24.000
We're pretty vulnerable here.

01:24.042 --> 01:26.670
Nobody was aware of truck bombs 
       in those days, really,

01:26.711 --> 01:27.754
you get right down to it.

01:27.796 --> 01:31.174
No one had really seen       
           suicide before.

01:31.216 --> 01:32.384
In other words,

01:32.426 --> 01:33.885
they're playing by rules      
            that we aren't.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.970
This was a new phenomenon.

01:36.012 --> 01:37.596
Who's doing this?

01:37.639 --> 01:39.641
dramatic music

01:53.654 --> 01:55.449
[indistinct chatter]

01:58.618 --> 02:00.412
[indistinct chatter]

02:17.179 --> 02:18.930
[taxi driver 1 speaking Arabic]

02:18.972 --> 02:20.724
[speaking Arabic]

02:23.642 --> 02:25.020
[taxi driver 2, in English]    
               Mister?

02:25.520 --> 02:26.938
[speaking Arabic]

02:26.980 --> 02:28.899
[taxi driver 2 speaking Arabic]

02:28.940 --> 02:30.066
[in English] Okay, good.

02:39.701 --> 02:41.369
[taxi driver 2 speaking Arabic]

02:41.411 --> 02:42.787
[in English]            
        What'd you do, swim?

02:42.829 --> 02:44.498
The flight was delayed.

02:44.539 --> 02:45.874
Never connect through Rome.

02:49.085 --> 02:50.128
I'm Steve.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.339
Chet.

02:53.089 --> 02:54.508
Welcome to Beirut, Chet.

02:57.260 --> 02:59.513
[fighter jet whooshing]

02:59.554 --> 03:01.348
[sirens wailing]

03:04.726 --> 03:06.478
What, are we across        
           the Green Line?

03:06.520 --> 03:08.730
Skirted round it.

03:08.772 --> 03:10.649
Did you put your hand up      
         for this shit show?

03:10.690 --> 03:12.150
Yep. I asked to come here.

03:12.984 --> 03:15.028
What, you like civil wars?

03:15.070 --> 03:17.113
[Chet] I was bored out of     
    my fucking mind in Khartoum.

03:17.154 --> 03:19.157
Plus, I knew Ames.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.367
[Steve] True believer, huh?

03:21.993 --> 03:22.953
Good for you.

03:26.581 --> 03:28.375
[crowd chanting in Arabic]

03:40.178 --> 03:41.388
[speaking Arabic]

04:27.392 --> 04:28.602
[guard, in English] Open up!

04:28.643 --> 04:30.270
[indistinct radio chatter]

04:36.401 --> 04:38.612
-This is us?            
           -[Steve] Yeah.

04:38.653 --> 04:41.323
Belonged to the Brits.       
        They took pity on us.

04:43.325 --> 04:44.200
[Chet] Jesus.

04:53.501 --> 04:54.502
[Chet sighs]

04:55.545 --> 04:56.755
[Steve] Mind your head.

04:59.633 --> 05:00.592
All right.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.178
Kitchen.

05:06.556 --> 05:07.641
Yeah.

05:07.682 --> 05:10.518
[sighs] I was on leave       
          when it happened.

05:13.480 --> 05:15.857
-You came through Cyprus?     
               -Rome.

05:17.359 --> 05:19.152
Try Cyprus next time.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.321
Thirty minutes and a world away.

05:21.946 --> 05:23.406
This is you.

05:23.448 --> 05:25.867
You think Buckley         
         is gonna read this?

05:25.909 --> 05:27.661
Listen, Buckley's         
      a little different, okay?

05:27.702 --> 05:29.996
He never trained          
         at the Farm, so...

05:30.038 --> 05:32.165
Ah. You must be Chet Riley.

05:32.207 --> 05:33.958
-Yeah.               
     -They say you speak Arabic.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.169
-A little.             
         -A little or a lot?

05:36.211 --> 05:38.171
-A lot.              
       -Ah. I hate languages.

05:39.464 --> 05:42.801
Well, this is all         
          we've got, boys.

05:42.842 --> 05:45.762
I asked Langley for more,     
           but go figure.

05:48.223 --> 05:50.016
Welcome to Operation Conestoga.

05:51.017 --> 05:52.644
We're here to find the assholes

05:52.686 --> 05:54.688
that killed            
      our brothers and sisters.

05:54.729 --> 05:57.732
Ames had a hunch about Iran.

05:57.774 --> 06:00.234
Some, uh, camp           
       near the Syrian border.

06:00.276 --> 06:01.653
Iran? Why would they be here?

06:01.695 --> 06:04.531
I mean, they're Persian,      
              not Arab.

06:04.572 --> 06:07.200
Thanks, Professor.         
          We all know that.

06:07.242 --> 06:09.327
I know. Just... I was saying    
       it doesn't make sense.

06:09.369 --> 06:11.496
Well, nothing makes sense     
            around here.

06:12.580 --> 06:13.623
All right.

06:13.665 --> 06:15.375
I got a meeting          
         with a Shia leader

06:15.417 --> 06:17.335
who thinks he's our best friend. 
            His name is--

06:17.377 --> 06:18.878
Nabih Berri, from Amal.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.005
You're gonna be my translator.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.258
Better get cleaned up.       
       You're coming with me.

06:23.299 --> 06:25.176
[Steve] All right,         
           let's do this.

06:25.218 --> 06:27.929
[Wyman]   Bill was          
          a unique character.

06:27.971 --> 06:29.347
He was a...

06:29.389 --> 06:31.641
He was a soldier of fortune,    
              I think,

06:31.683 --> 06:34.060
in the old school sense.

06:34.102 --> 06:37.021
His job was            
      to try to sort things out

06:37.063 --> 06:38.732
on the ground in Lebanon.

06:38.773 --> 06:40.608
Build something          
           out of the ashes.

06:41.276 --> 06:42.318
I read your file.

06:43.445 --> 06:44.571
Army grunt, huh?

06:45.947 --> 06:47.991
I enlisted, took a test.

06:48.032 --> 06:49.409
Turns out             
      I was good at languages.

06:49.451 --> 06:51.453
[chuckling] Next thing you know, 
          I'm at the Farm.

06:52.954 --> 06:54.414
Just watch out           
        for the Ivy Leaguers.

06:58.460 --> 07:00.503
-You were Special Forces?     
             -5th Group.

07:01.421 --> 07:02.380
Then I went to the Agency.

07:03.131 --> 07:04.257
[clears throat]

07:04.299 --> 07:05.883
-Sounded good at the time.     
            -[door opens]

07:05.925 --> 07:08.511
Egypt, Saudi.           
      Kicking around, you know.

07:10.305 --> 07:11.139
Yep.

07:13.475 --> 07:15.351
[Nabih speaking Arabic]

07:15.393 --> 07:16.603
[man chuckles]

07:17.312 --> 07:18.146
Oh.

07:20.523 --> 07:21.775
[in English] Mr. Buckley.

07:21.816 --> 07:23.359
-Welcome to Lebanon.        
             -Thank you.

07:23.401 --> 07:24.944
How can I be of assistance?

07:24.986 --> 07:27.864
-Mr. Berri--            
       -Please, call me Nabih.

07:27.906 --> 07:29.616
Or more simply, Abu Hassan.

07:29.991 --> 07:30.992
Okay.

07:31.034 --> 07:32.368
Mr. Abu Hassan,

07:32.410 --> 07:34.078
we're trying to figure out     
       who bombed our embassy.

07:42.003 --> 07:44.214
America has many enemies.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.133
I know that.

07:47.175 --> 07:50.261
What about that group of Shia   
        working out of Iran?

07:50.303 --> 07:52.555
[Nabih] I will tell you      
      what I told Robert Ames.

07:53.264 --> 07:54.808
This group is nothing.

07:54.849 --> 07:56.643
Too small and weak.

07:56.684 --> 07:59.604
Well, Ames is dead,        
   maybe because he believed you.

08:01.773 --> 08:04.108
[speaking Arabic]

08:04.150 --> 08:05.234
[in English]            
        Have a seat, please.

08:06.194 --> 08:07.153
Sure.

08:08.403 --> 08:09.321
Thank you.

08:10.739 --> 08:11.825
[Buckley clears throat]

08:17.372 --> 08:19.332
Have you heard           
       about Sheikh Fadlallah?

08:20.250 --> 08:21.918
Mm-mm. No.

08:21.960 --> 08:24.879
They say              
    he is their spiritual leader.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.423
Their imam.

08:27.465 --> 08:29.509
We do have a source        
       who may know something.

08:30.385 --> 08:31.845
We can ask him.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.346
I'd like to ask          
         your source myself.

08:34.097 --> 08:35.473
That will not be possible.

08:38.685 --> 08:40.186
How's your wife liking Dearborn?

08:40.937 --> 08:42.564
Lila.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.065
Do your kids have         
        their passports yet,

08:44.107 --> 08:45.567
or are they            
      still using green cards?

08:46.651 --> 08:49.028
You have              
      a green card too, right?

08:49.070 --> 08:52.073
Those things come up for renewal 
       at the strangest times.

08:55.910 --> 08:57.745
He told a joke           
         when I went inside.

08:57.787 --> 08:59.372
What was it?

08:59.414 --> 09:00.540
He, uh... [chuckles]

09:02.083 --> 09:03.626
Uh, he said            
      you look like a penguin.

09:07.297 --> 09:08.423
[chuckles] That's a good one.

09:08.464 --> 09:09.507
[Chet chuckles]

09:11.426 --> 09:12.552
I got a job for you.

09:15.847 --> 09:17.223
[Mustafa speaking Arabic]

09:30.737 --> 09:32.071
[Haidar speaking]

09:34.449 --> 09:35.366
[Imad speaking]

09:36.534 --> 09:37.869
[Fadlallah speaking]

10:16.658 --> 10:18.117
[children giggling]

10:19.661 --> 10:21.788
[child, in English]        
         Pepsi, Fanta, 7Up!

10:25.166 --> 10:27.335
Pepsi, Fanta, 7Up!

10:28.336 --> 10:30.630
Pepsi, Fanta, 7Up!

10:32.674 --> 10:34.926
Pepsi, Fanta, 7Up!

10:37.136 --> 10:38.930
Pepsi, Fanta, 7Up...

10:42.892 --> 10:44.394
[Fadlallah speaking Arabic]

10:51.693 --> 10:53.653
[audience chattering        
            in agreement]

11:06.708 --> 11:08.167
[indistinct chatter]

11:11.212 --> 11:14.257
[man on tape speaking Arabic]

11:21.472 --> 11:23.516
[Steve, in English] Okay,     
        here's a 50K transfer

11:23.558 --> 11:24.684
through Sierra Leone.

11:27.228 --> 11:28.688
What, is this           
      the same trading company?

11:28.730 --> 11:30.106
Mm-mm. Diamonds this time.

11:35.903 --> 11:37.655
-These guys are good.       
              -Mm-hmm.

11:41.367 --> 11:42.326
[Imad speaking Arabic]

11:46.748 --> 11:47.623
[door closes]

13:26.097 --> 13:28.141
[Arabic music playing]

13:30.268 --> 13:32.645
[indistinct chatter]

13:47.869 --> 13:49.245
[speaking Arabic]

13:57.920 --> 13:58.713
[chuckles]

14:11.559 --> 14:12.602
[in English] Do you mind?

14:12.643 --> 14:13.728
No. Suit yourself.

14:15.688 --> 14:16.647
Thank you.

14:18.816 --> 14:20.860
She call me a penguin, too?

14:20.902 --> 14:23.070
-You really wanna know?      
         -[Buckley chuckles]

14:31.871 --> 14:33.873
Look, I know            
      you really admired Ames.

14:34.916 --> 14:37.210
But we're very different.

14:37.251 --> 14:39.545
Yeah, he was a good man      
       who believed in people.

14:39.587 --> 14:41.631
[chuckles] Okay. Listen to you.

14:43.507 --> 14:44.467
You got a family?

14:45.718 --> 14:47.136
I've been in the field too long.

15:02.151 --> 15:04.111
[man] Only you. Alone.

15:05.196 --> 15:07.073
-Yeah.               
     -[Buckley] It's all right.

15:10.243 --> 15:12.245
I hear you have some information 
         about the embassy.

15:14.956 --> 15:16.499
If anyone sees me here,      
              I'm done.

15:16.540 --> 15:17.583
-You understand?          
                -Yes.

15:19.335 --> 15:21.462
Whoa. Slowly.

15:21.504 --> 15:22.880
It's just my fucking cigarettes.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.423
What's wrong with you?

15:29.971 --> 15:31.222
[Buckley] If you have       
          something to say,

15:31.264 --> 15:32.598
now would be the time to say it.

15:33.808 --> 15:35.142
I'll make it worth your while.

15:39.146 --> 15:40.773
They call themselves        
           Islamic Jihad.

15:40.815 --> 15:42.942
I know that. I need        
      the name of their leader.

15:42.984 --> 15:46.112
-He's a ghost.           
          -Give me a break.

15:46.153 --> 15:49.115
Hey, listen, I'm a businessman, 
    okay? And I love my country.

15:49.156 --> 15:51.242
And I hate to see what these    
   fanatics want to turn it into.

15:51.284 --> 15:52.660
I need specifics.

16:00.001 --> 16:03.546
Okay. Two more trucks       
     are already here in Beirut.

16:03.587 --> 16:04.922
They will come for your embassy,

16:04.964 --> 16:06.299
the one you share         
          with the British,

16:07.008 --> 16:07.841
very soon.

16:08.843 --> 16:09.760
Anything else?

16:12.138 --> 16:13.973
Mm. Yeah.

16:16.726 --> 16:19.020
The man you want,         
        they call him Radwan.

16:19.061 --> 16:20.146
Hajj Radwan.

16:23.983 --> 16:24.817
How do you know all this?

16:26.986 --> 16:28.654
I sold them the explosives.

16:32.533 --> 16:34.534
tense music

16:38.872 --> 16:41.125
The guy's got burn notice     
        written all over him.

16:41.167 --> 16:43.168
Write him up. Code name Alpha.

16:43.210 --> 16:44.837
Our first source in New Lebanon.

16:46.380 --> 16:48.381
And warn the embassies.      
     We gotta find those trucks.

16:49.966 --> 16:52.345
[Chet] You sure?          
 I mean, it's a big fucking city.

16:52.386 --> 16:53.971
Uh, can the Marines        
            help us look?

16:54.013 --> 16:55.598
Yeah, there's an Arabic word

16:55.639 --> 16:57.183
for getting them          
    out of their comfy barracks.

16:57.224 --> 16:58.601
Even I know that one.

16:58.642 --> 16:59.894
[Chet]   Inshallah.

16:59.935 --> 17:01.145
[Buckley] As in never.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.314
No, we're on our own.

17:04.273 --> 17:07.026
-You gonna offer me a ride?    
                -No.

17:07.068 --> 17:08.778
Go back inside, have some fun.

17:08.819 --> 17:09.695
See you bright and early.

17:12.114 --> 17:13.699
[engine starts]

17:17.536 --> 17:19.038
[speaking Arabic]

17:25.211 --> 17:26.212
[Mustafa speaking]

17:33.094 --> 17:34.011
Uh...

17:47.942 --> 17:49.276
[Imad speaking]

18:18.180 --> 18:21.016
[in English] All right,      
         take south Beirut.

18:21.058 --> 18:22.852
You two, take the west of town.

18:22.893 --> 18:25.729
Chet and I'll take the Corniche 
      and warehouse districts.

18:25.771 --> 18:26.730
Find 'em!

18:35.865 --> 18:37.533
[Chet] 7:00 a.m. again, boss.

18:37.575 --> 18:39.076
You wanna switch that up?

18:39.118 --> 18:39.994
Fuck off.

18:43.539 --> 18:44.748
What are you gonna do?

18:49.670 --> 18:52.298
[Daqduq speaking Arabic]

19:03.476 --> 19:04.477
[Haidar speaking]

19:06.395 --> 19:07.271
[Imad] Haidar.

19:28.876 --> 19:30.836
[in English] Did this Alpha    
       Boy Scout you recruited

19:30.878 --> 19:32.254
give us a fucking clue, or what?

19:32.296 --> 19:33.714
I didn't recruit him.

19:33.756 --> 19:36.133
Two trucks somewhere in Beirut, 
       targeting the embassy.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.260
[Steve] Ah. That's...

19:38.302 --> 19:39.345
That's great intel.

19:40.888 --> 19:42.765
It's a shitty building anyway.   
        They can blow it up.

19:42.806 --> 19:44.725
We'll just give it back      
            to the Brits.

20:00.699 --> 20:02.284
-There.              
            -Yeah, yeah.

20:04.537 --> 20:06.121
[tires screech]

20:09.083 --> 20:10.376
-Out the way, out the way!     
            -[horn beeps]

20:10.417 --> 20:11.794
Move, move, move, move!

20:13.420 --> 20:14.421
[hawker yells]

20:15.923 --> 20:17.967
tense music

20:32.940 --> 20:35.734
[Arabic music playing       
           on loudspeaker]

20:44.285 --> 20:45.953
These wogs all look        
           the same to me.

20:46.787 --> 20:48.372
Come on. That doesn't help.

20:48.414 --> 20:49.582
[chuckles]

20:49.623 --> 20:51.083
Don't go native on us, Chet.

21:12.980 --> 21:13.939
[Chet] Hey, uh, boss.

21:14.940 --> 21:16.609
Yeah, we've been everywhere.    
              Nothing.

21:17.818 --> 21:18.819
I see.

21:20.154 --> 21:21.905
[Chet]   What about the others?

21:21.947 --> 21:24.074
We found two vegetable trucks,   
           a garbage truck

21:24.116 --> 21:26.368
and one full of junk        
       and searched them all.

21:27.828 --> 21:29.622
Alpha might've been playing us.

21:29.663 --> 21:30.789
Maybe.

21:30.831 --> 21:32.374
But the embassy          
       looks like a fortress.

21:32.416 --> 21:34.752
We've warned the Marines      
           and our allies.

21:34.793 --> 21:36.128
Go home, get some rest.

21:36.170 --> 21:37.463
We can keep going.

21:37.504 --> 21:38.714
I said get some rest, right?

21:39.673 --> 21:40.966
Okay. Copy that.

21:46.055 --> 21:46.930
[sighs]

21:49.516 --> 21:50.768
He said to call it a night.

21:52.061 --> 21:52.936
Really?

21:53.854 --> 21:55.147
He said, "Get some rest."

21:56.815 --> 21:58.984
-He's an odd one.         
         -Tell me about it.

22:02.446 --> 22:04.281
[Steve] You know, uh,       
        he's dating a recruit

22:04.323 --> 22:05.616
back at the Farm,

22:05.658 --> 22:07.284
twenty-five years old.

22:07.326 --> 22:09.787
Apparently, he really likes her,

22:09.828 --> 22:11.330
along with             
       a couple dozen others.

22:12.539 --> 22:14.875
-Buckley? Really?         
          -[chuckles] Yup.

22:15.876 --> 22:17.503
You know,             
     I don't know what's worse.

22:18.045 --> 22:19.088
Being single here

22:19.129 --> 22:20.130
or thinking            
        about your girlfriend

22:20.172 --> 22:21.590
fucking someone else back home.

22:24.677 --> 22:25.678
[Steve chuckles softly]

22:26.553 --> 22:27.513
You got someone?

22:28.305 --> 22:29.181
Yeah.

22:30.057 --> 22:30.933
Serious?

22:32.226 --> 22:33.352
Pretty serious.

22:34.895 --> 22:36.355
Why the fuck are you here?

22:38.899 --> 22:40.526
Thought              
     I could make a difference.

22:40.567 --> 22:41.819
Oh.

22:41.860 --> 22:43.112
Another true believer, huh?

22:49.910 --> 22:51.203
[explosion in the distance]

22:53.580 --> 22:54.456
Up, up!

22:56.375 --> 22:58.085
Oh, fuck.

23:01.255 --> 23:02.423
That's not the embassy.

23:04.425 --> 23:06.051
It's not even fucking close.

23:07.720 --> 23:08.929
[explosion in the distance]

23:11.557 --> 23:13.559
melancholic music

23:24.445 --> 23:26.488
The search goes on         
           for more victims

23:26.530 --> 23:29.658
in today's murderous attacks    
      on the Marine headquarters,

23:29.700 --> 23:31.368
and a building           
        housing French troops.

23:31.410 --> 23:34.246
[reporter 1]   Between 250      
           and 300 Americans

23:34.288 --> 23:36.915
were in the building        
 when the suicide bomber struck.

23:36.957 --> 23:39.084
As snipers             
        distracted the guards,

23:39.126 --> 23:42.755
a man in a truck laden with    
      2,000 pounds of explosives

23:42.796 --> 23:44.506
raced toward his target.

23:44.548 --> 23:45.716
[Peter Jennings]   It was just

23:45.758 --> 23:47.134
after 9:30 in Kuwait        
             this morning

23:47.176 --> 23:48.761
when a truck            
        loaded with explosives

23:48.802 --> 23:51.263
crashed through the gates     
      of the US embassy compound

23:51.305 --> 23:52.973
and blew up.

23:53.015 --> 23:55.309
[reporter 2]   Within two hours,   
      another five bombs went off

23:55.350 --> 23:57.102
in sites all over Kuwait.

23:57.144 --> 24:00.063
The bombs apparently hidden    
        in booby-trapped cars.

24:00.105 --> 24:01.648
[reporter 3]            
          Who is responsible?

24:01.690 --> 24:04.610
A radical terrorist group     
         called Islamic Jihad,

24:04.651 --> 24:07.446
or Islamic Holy War,        
          has claimed credit.

24:07.488 --> 24:09.281
[reporter 4]   It's the       
     same group which earlier said

24:09.323 --> 24:11.617
it blew up the American embassy   
               in Beirut

24:11.658 --> 24:13.786
and the Marine headquarters    
              in Lebanon.

24:13.827 --> 24:15.621
[reporter 5]   The White House    
         is under new pressure

24:15.662 --> 24:18.040
to justify the presence      
       of American peacekeepers

24:18.081 --> 24:19.500
on the ground in Lebanon.

24:24.671 --> 24:26.131
There was nothing else       
            we could do.

24:26.173 --> 24:28.759
Six bombs, all in minutes.

24:28.801 --> 24:31.136
Who the fuck are these guys?

24:31.178 --> 24:33.639
Hey, boss wants          
        everyone downstairs.

24:38.644 --> 24:39.478
[Buckley] Gentlemen.

24:41.688 --> 24:43.524
I just got a call         
        from Director Casey.

24:46.026 --> 24:48.445
Apparently, the White House    
        is done with Lebanon.

24:48.487 --> 24:51.156
The Marines, the battleships,   
       everyone's pulling out.

24:53.242 --> 24:55.160
So the message is         
          hit America hard,

24:55.202 --> 24:57.496
and then we just          
        fucking cut and run?

24:57.538 --> 24:58.872
Seems like.

24:58.914 --> 25:01.250
And don't think          
     the bad guys won't notice.

25:01.291 --> 25:03.126
[Steve] And what about us?

25:03.168 --> 25:04.586
[Buckley]             
      That's a personal choice.

25:04.628 --> 25:06.046
I won't force anyone to stay.

25:13.846 --> 25:15.097
Appreciate it.

25:15.138 --> 25:16.515
Let's get back to work.

25:19.226 --> 25:20.644
[Tom Brokaw]            
       President Reagan tonight

25:20.686 --> 25:23.480
ordered a phased pullback     
          of American Marines

25:23.522 --> 25:26.066
from their positions        
      around the Beirut airport.

25:26.108 --> 25:27.651
That announcement         
           came this evening

25:27.693 --> 25:30.028
after the Lebanese forces     
      backed by the United States

25:30.070 --> 25:32.030
took a terrible beating today.

25:32.072 --> 25:33.031
The Marines will be...

25:33.073 --> 25:34.116
Thanks for everything.

25:38.579 --> 25:40.205
-[knocking at door]        
          -[Buckley] Chet.

25:40.247 --> 25:41.373
[door closes]

25:42.749 --> 25:43.625
Listen.

25:45.919 --> 25:47.129
I've been around long enough

25:47.170 --> 25:49.548
to recognize a sinking ship    
           when I see one.

25:49.590 --> 25:51.633
Especially when          
        I'm standing on deck.

25:51.675 --> 25:53.468
You do not want this stain     
           on your record.

25:56.054 --> 25:57.222
I can find this guy.

25:59.474 --> 26:03.896
Well, you're even more stupid   
           than I thought.

26:03.937 --> 26:05.397
-[knocking at door]        
          -[Buckley] Yeah.

26:06.732 --> 26:09.234
The guys who hit Kuwait.      
   Found them. Seventeen of them.

26:09.276 --> 26:11.737
Including one guy from Lebanon. 
              Let's go.

26:17.034 --> 26:18.702
[news playing           
         indistinctly on TV]

26:20.037 --> 26:21.580
[Haidar speaking Arabic]

26:35.969 --> 26:36.929
[Imad sighs]

26:41.099 --> 26:43.101
[Imad clicks tongue, sighs]

27:10.253 --> 27:13.423
[Saada sighs]

27:19.805 --> 27:21.348
[sobbing softly]

27:21.390 --> 27:24.977
[in English] Mustafa Badreddine 
     had traveled out to Kuwait,

27:25.018 --> 27:26.770
did a bombing there        
          and was captured.

27:26.812 --> 27:29.648
An American professor at the    
    American University of Beirut

27:29.690 --> 27:33.110
was kidnapped as he was coming    
         from Beirut airport.

27:33.151 --> 27:35.654
[Dan Rather]   Another American   
     has been kidnapped in Beirut.

27:37.197 --> 27:38.782
[Wyman]   All this          
         awful stuff going on,

27:38.824 --> 27:40.492
and it just creates        
             a situation,

27:40.534 --> 27:43.620
an atmosphere, an aura       
         of why are we here?

27:43.662 --> 27:45.163
What's the point?

27:45.205 --> 27:46.832
[Gary Berntsen]   So many      
         of these kidnappings

27:46.873 --> 27:49.126
that take place          
          in the late 1980s,

27:49.167 --> 27:51.003
are all conducted         
          because Mughniyeh

27:51.044 --> 27:54.214
is trying to free         
         his brother-in-law.

27:55.173 --> 27:56.508
What do you got?

27:56.550 --> 27:58.135
[Chet] This Islamic Jihad group

27:58.176 --> 28:01.346
is demanding that we release    
         Mustafa Badreddine,

28:01.388 --> 28:03.640
who's the guy in jail in Kuwait,

28:03.682 --> 28:05.600
in return             
     for some of these hostages.

28:05.642 --> 28:07.936
[Buckley] Who the hell       
       is Mustafa Badreddine?

28:07.978 --> 28:09.688
We don't know.

28:09.730 --> 28:11.356
Can we get to him in Kuwait?

28:11.398 --> 28:13.775
Well, Kuwaitis won't help.     
     They'll probably kill him.

28:13.817 --> 28:15.235
Was he with those assholes

28:15.277 --> 28:16.570
you saw hanging out        
           at that mosque?

28:16.611 --> 28:18.488
Half of south Beirut        
      hangs out at that mosque.

28:18.530 --> 28:20.198
Time to talk to Alpha.

28:21.992 --> 28:23.744
[men speaking Arabic]

28:23.785 --> 28:25.579
[Arabic music           
        playing on speakers]

28:31.918 --> 28:32.753
[speaking Arabic]

28:35.422 --> 28:37.215
[urgent footsteps]

28:43.889 --> 28:46.725
[Steve, in English]   All right.   
       I'm gonna ask you again.

28:48.268 --> 28:49.394
Who is Radwan?

28:50.103 --> 28:51.521
Is he Mustafa Badreddine?

28:51.563 --> 28:53.231
Mustafa? No, that's not him.

28:53.273 --> 28:54.316
It's okay.

28:55.734 --> 28:56.902
I'm here to help you.

29:04.576 --> 29:06.203
They call him   Abu Dukhan,

29:06.244 --> 29:08.663
father of the smoke,        
       because he disappears.

29:09.915 --> 29:12.042
Father of the smoke? Really?

29:12.084 --> 29:13.835
Let's just hand him        
          to the Israelis.

29:13.877 --> 29:15.170
[Alpha] Come on, guys. Really?

29:15.879 --> 29:17.881
We need a real name, okay?

29:17.923 --> 29:19.091
Can you do that for us?

29:20.383 --> 29:22.094
-Give me a real name?       
               -Fuck.

29:23.512 --> 29:25.764
[Buckley] Come on.         
    Think about your own future.

29:28.725 --> 29:29.976
Imad. [sighs]

29:30.018 --> 29:31.269
Imad Mughniyeh.

29:31.311 --> 29:34.147
Mughniyeh? How old is he?     
          Where's he from?

29:34.189 --> 29:35.816
-I don't know.           
         -Who's he work for?

29:36.608 --> 29:38.068
Can I have my money now?

29:38.110 --> 29:41.905
I think you want          
     more than money, don't you?

29:42.656 --> 29:43.657
[Chet] Who's he working for?

29:44.533 --> 29:46.409
Fadlallah? Iran? Why hit Kuwait?

29:46.451 --> 29:48.328
I don't fucking know.       
          I never saw him.

29:48.370 --> 29:49.454
No one saw him.

29:49.496 --> 29:51.331
You've never seen...        
         No one's seen him?

29:52.040 --> 29:53.750
Come on.

29:53.792 --> 29:56.002
If you've got something      
      to offer, now's the time.

30:10.642 --> 30:11.726
They say he wants to lead

30:11.768 --> 30:12.853
the Shia of Lebanon.

30:13.520 --> 30:15.147
Begin our revolution.

30:15.188 --> 30:16.815
I mean, who can blame him?

30:16.857 --> 30:17.816
We need a revolution.

30:18.358 --> 30:20.318
But not that kind.

30:20.360 --> 30:21.987
[Buckley] You would do it     
     differently, wouldn't you?

30:22.028 --> 30:23.155
Yeah.

30:23.196 --> 30:26.074
I'll choose my friends       
           more carefully.

30:26.116 --> 30:28.869
Where is he?            
       Where can we find him?

30:28.910 --> 30:31.246
Honestly, guys, I swear,      
    I told you everything I know.

30:33.331 --> 30:35.417
Okay. Okay.

30:37.669 --> 30:38.795
[door opens]

30:41.840 --> 30:42.674
[door closes]

30:43.216 --> 30:44.092
I don't trust him.

30:46.178 --> 30:47.179
Check that name.

30:49.389 --> 30:51.683
[indistinct chatter in Arabic]

31:04.571 --> 31:07.115
[Chet, in English] All right,   
        I checked everything.

31:07.157 --> 31:08.283
Marriage certificates,

31:08.325 --> 31:09.951
school records,          
         birth certificates.

31:09.993 --> 31:11.536
There's nothing on the name    
           Imad Mughniyeh.

31:11.578 --> 31:12.871
I mean, the fucking name      
           doesn't exist.

31:12.913 --> 31:14.539
Fuck. I knew Alpha was lying.

31:14.581 --> 31:16.041
Okay, that's what I thought.

31:16.082 --> 31:17.792
But then I had this guy      
       at the passport office

31:17.834 --> 31:19.711
pull photos from an old archive 
           in a warehouse,

31:19.753 --> 31:20.712
just on a hunch.

31:26.176 --> 31:27.636
That's our guy.

31:27.677 --> 31:30.138
Kid from the slums,        
        maybe five years ago.

31:31.598 --> 31:32.599
That's our guy.

31:34.267 --> 31:36.353
[Buckley] So what,         
        is he, like, 20 now?

31:36.394 --> 31:37.270
[Chet] Yeah.

31:39.814 --> 31:42.275
[folk music playing on speakers]

31:42.317 --> 31:44.110
[Buckley] Now we know       
 who's fucking us. What a relief.

31:45.779 --> 31:47.948
Right. So we track him down.

31:47.989 --> 31:49.866
With our manpower,         
        that could take ages.

31:49.908 --> 31:50.909
No offense.

31:54.663 --> 31:55.664
Listen, Bill,

31:57.749 --> 32:00.835
you got to vary your routine    
            or something.

32:00.877 --> 32:03.546
You can't keep dressing like    
    an ad man on Madison Avenue.

32:03.588 --> 32:04.965
What are you, my ex-wife?

32:05.006 --> 32:06.549
[Chet] Or your           
       25-year-old girlfriend.

32:08.218 --> 32:09.427
[Buckley] You know about that?

32:10.929 --> 32:12.430
We were hoping           
      to keep that as a secret

32:12.472 --> 32:14.099
since she's also in the Agency.

32:16.893 --> 32:18.019
You have someone you like?

32:19.145 --> 32:19.980
No.

32:22.274 --> 32:23.108
Well, you should.

32:26.152 --> 32:28.780
I'm gonna call it a night.     
     You take it easy, brother.

32:39.332 --> 32:42.002
[alarm buzzing]

32:43.003 --> 32:44.045
[urinating]

32:45.839 --> 32:48.591
[breathing rhythmically]

33:17.871 --> 33:19.164
[engine starts]

33:24.878 --> 33:26.838
[men speaking Arabic]

33:39.225 --> 33:40.935
[tires screeching]

33:40.977 --> 33:42.687
[kettle whistling]

33:46.900 --> 33:48.692
-[Steve, in English] Morning.   
                -Hey.

33:48.735 --> 33:50.319
Uh, you seen the boss?

33:50.362 --> 33:52.238
Have you heard from him?      
          It's after 7:00.

33:52.279 --> 33:53.698
Is he not in his office?

33:53.739 --> 33:54.783
[Chet] I don't think so.

33:57.451 --> 33:58.620
-[knocking]            
           -[Steve] Bill.

34:18.056 --> 34:20.100
[Chet speaking Arabic]

34:33.696 --> 34:36.241
[Steve, in English] Yes, sir.   
        Sat phone, contacts.

34:36.282 --> 34:37.575
All our assets are lost.

34:37.617 --> 34:39.994
Jesus Christ.

34:40.036 --> 34:41.496
Well, did you warn the assets?

34:42.789 --> 34:43.665
Some.

34:44.624 --> 34:46.793
We think this is Islamic Jihad.

34:48.586 --> 34:50.422
[Casey]   Who the hell's that?    
         Who the hell is this?

34:50.463 --> 34:52.048
[Dewey]   It's, uh...        
           It's Chet Riley.

34:52.090 --> 34:53.591
He's a case officer.

34:53.633 --> 34:54.968
[Casey punches table lightly]

34:55.009 --> 34:56.594
All right.

34:56.636 --> 34:59.931
Case Officer, we got any light   
         inside this group?

34:59.973 --> 35:01.057
[Chet]   Yes, we have Alpha.

35:01.099 --> 35:02.600
[Casey]   Who's Alpha?

35:02.642 --> 35:03.726
[Chet] He's a source.

35:03.768 --> 35:05.311
He could be playing us.      
           We don't know.

35:05.353 --> 35:07.272
He gave us the name for Radwan.

35:08.481 --> 35:09.649
[Casey]   Radwan? Who's Radwan?

35:12.318 --> 35:14.946
The leader of this group,     
              we think.

35:14.988 --> 35:17.157
Okay. What's the name?

35:17.198 --> 35:19.617
[Chet]   Imad Mughniyeh.

35:19.659 --> 35:22.912
He probably hit our embassy,    
        the Marines, Kuwait.

35:22.954 --> 35:25.123
I think it's safe to assume    
        he has Buckley, too.

35:26.583 --> 35:29.294
-[Casey]   What's his name?     
          -Imad Mughniyeh.

35:29.335 --> 35:30.628
Twenty-one years old.

35:31.504 --> 35:32.797
[Casey]   God damn it.

35:32.839 --> 35:34.090
What, I'm supposed         
        to tell the President

35:34.132 --> 35:35.842
some punk kid           
       has our station chief?

35:36.968 --> 35:37.802
Huh?

35:40.263 --> 35:42.474
He's gonna ask me         
   how long Buckley can hold out.

35:44.350 --> 35:45.643
He's sentimental that way.

35:47.604 --> 35:49.439
Bill's a Green Beret, sir.

35:49.481 --> 35:50.982
He'll hold out           
         as long as he can.

35:52.358 --> 35:54.152
All right.

35:54.194 --> 35:55.904
Let me know            
        if you hear anything.

35:55.945 --> 35:57.322
Understand, Case Officer?

35:57.780 --> 35:58.656
Yes, sir.

35:59.324 --> 36:01.534
Uh, sir, one more thing.

36:01.576 --> 36:04.329
We have intercepts here      
       that tie back to Iran.

36:04.370 --> 36:06.789
It's possible they're pulling   
     the strings on all of this.

36:08.583 --> 36:09.876
Just find Buckley.

36:11.294 --> 36:12.504
[line buzzing]

36:17.467 --> 36:19.344
[door creaks open]

36:21.930 --> 36:23.515
[footsteps approaching]

36:45.078 --> 36:47.872
[Imad, in English] Sorry.     
        This is all we have.

36:52.085 --> 36:53.211
Radwan.

37:03.263 --> 37:05.974
I need you to tell me       
          about Kuwait 17.

37:08.685 --> 37:10.687
I know you have          
         Mustafa Badreddine.

37:11.312 --> 37:12.230
No.

37:13.606 --> 37:15.400
No. The Kuwaitis have him.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.235
Come on.

37:18.111 --> 37:19.362
You're CIA.

37:25.326 --> 37:26.202
Eat.

37:27.787 --> 37:30.873
You'll be here for a long time,

37:30.915 --> 37:34.419
Mr. William Francis Buckley.

37:58.067 --> 37:58.943
[grunts]

38:04.907 --> 38:06.200
[sniffing]

38:08.995 --> 38:10.955
[reporter speaking Arabic on TV]

38:19.339 --> 38:21.341
[reporter continues]

38:32.935 --> 38:34.270
[speaking Arabic]

39:40.211 --> 39:41.045
[sniffles]

39:56.519 --> 39:57.770
[speaking Arabic]

40:11.284 --> 40:12.118
[in English] Okay.

40:13.953 --> 40:14.954
What's your name?

40:17.457 --> 40:18.666
I'm not making a tape.

40:21.043 --> 40:22.253
[clears throat]

40:22.295 --> 40:24.756
[Imad] I want           
        your friends to know

40:24.797 --> 40:27.925
that I have your, uh,       
           CIA briefcase,

40:29.010 --> 40:30.178
your special phone,

40:31.971 --> 40:32.889
and I have you.

40:35.850 --> 40:36.768
So talk.

40:40.480 --> 40:41.564
[softly] No.

40:43.191 --> 40:44.400
[Imad sighs]

40:45.485 --> 40:46.652
[Buckley grunting]

41:03.336 --> 41:05.379
[Alpha] Hey, guys, you good?

41:07.173 --> 41:08.800
-Hey.               
           -[Alpha] Yeah.

41:08.841 --> 41:10.343
I have something for you.

41:12.512 --> 41:13.805
Proof of life.

41:13.846 --> 41:14.972
[Imad speaking Arabic]

41:22.605 --> 41:24.148
[Chet, in English]         
           This is Buckley?

41:24.190 --> 41:25.316
Where'd you get this?

41:26.359 --> 41:28.611
-Where is he?           
           -I don't know.

41:28.653 --> 41:29.695
Where'd you get the tape?

41:30.112 --> 41:30.988
Guys.

41:33.908 --> 41:35.368
He trusted you.          
        You understand that?

41:35.409 --> 41:37.036
Come on, man.           
         Hey, hey, hey, hey.

41:37.078 --> 41:38.621
-He trusted you.          
        -Back off, back off.

41:38.663 --> 41:41.165
I'm just a fucking messenger.   
       What's wrong with you?

41:41.207 --> 41:43.292
-I'm here to help.         
             -All right.

41:43.334 --> 41:45.127
I understand that.

41:45.169 --> 41:47.463
I just need you to tell me     
        where the fuck he is.

41:47.505 --> 41:49.674
-Yeah, I get it.          
      -Yeah. Is he at Baalbek?

41:49.715 --> 41:51.342
-Where is he?           
      -Don't fucking touch me.

41:51.384 --> 41:53.386
You know what? Watch the tape.   
       It's very entertaining.

41:53.427 --> 41:54.387
Watch it.

41:58.099 --> 41:59.225
[Alpha grunting]

42:03.604 --> 42:04.730
[Steve] Jesus, Chet.

42:07.066 --> 42:08.192
Keep going like that.

42:09.569 --> 42:11.279
You'll get             
     fucking Buckley in pieces!

42:11.320 --> 42:13.948
I asked you,            
        where the fuck is he?

42:13.990 --> 42:14.866
Fuck you!

42:17.910 --> 42:20.037
Damn it, Chet! Back off.

42:53.779 --> 42:55.907
They had broken the CIA,

42:55.948 --> 42:57.950
not only with           
     the Marine Corps bombing...

42:57.992 --> 43:00.745
The Marines,            
       United States Marines.

43:00.786 --> 43:02.914
And now they've got        
          a station chief.

43:02.955 --> 43:06.167
Buckley was tortured        
          horribly by them.

43:06.208 --> 43:09.420
There were videos         
        that were sent back.

43:09.462 --> 43:13.466
They took an electric drill    
             to joints.

43:14.717 --> 43:16.135
And you don't forget that.

43:17.803 --> 43:19.597
You're breathless

43:19.639 --> 43:21.098
when you see that         
         for the first time.

43:22.308 --> 43:23.142
Sorry.

43:24.644 --> 43:25.686
Sorry.

43:25.728 --> 43:27.438
I hadn't done that         
         in a while. Sorry.

43:29.148 --> 43:29.982
I'm good.

43:40.159 --> 43:42.954
My name is             
       William Francis Buckley.

43:44.664 --> 43:46.123
I work for the CIA.

43:46.999 --> 43:48.292
[Dewey softly] God damn it.

43:48.334 --> 43:50.628
[drill whirring on TV]

43:50.670 --> 43:51.796
Oh, no.

43:51.837 --> 43:53.422
[Buckley screaming]

43:53.464 --> 43:54.465
Oh, no.

43:55.174 --> 43:56.217
[Casey on phone]   Oh, no.

43:57.885 --> 44:00.805
[screaming continues]

44:01.847 --> 44:02.682
Is anyone there?

44:04.892 --> 44:06.310
[clears throat]          
          Yeah, it's Dewey.

44:07.520 --> 44:08.938
Jesus Christ, Chet.

44:08.980 --> 44:10.690
Sir, I need to go to Baalbek.

44:10.731 --> 44:12.274
There's a very good chance     
           Buckley's there

44:12.316 --> 44:13.693
in that Iranian training camp.

44:13.734 --> 44:14.902
[Dewey]   No, you're gonna      
              stand down.

44:14.944 --> 44:16.278
That's far too risky.

44:16.320 --> 44:18.656
How the fuck do you propose    
         I get him out, sir?

44:22.034 --> 44:23.244
[Dewey]   I'll get back to you.

44:23.285 --> 44:24.996
[call disconnects]

44:25.037 --> 44:26.998
[reporter on TV]   The group     
      that claimed responsibility

44:27.039 --> 44:28.833
for the bombings          
          of the US embassies

44:28.874 --> 44:31.002
and the Marine base        
          recently announced

44:31.043 --> 44:33.838
that it's holding         
     all five kidnapped Americans.

44:33.879 --> 44:35.089
And it...

44:39.802 --> 44:40.678
I'm going to Baalbek.

44:42.054 --> 44:43.014
You can't.

44:43.055 --> 44:44.348
Fuck it. Are you coming?

44:45.725 --> 44:48.686
-Who you talking to?        
      -No one. [clears throat]

44:52.231 --> 44:55.026
[Steve] Damn it.          
      Yeah, Dewey, he's going.

45:03.993 --> 45:05.786
There's gonna be          
       a crossroads up ahead.

45:05.828 --> 45:06.996
We're gonna go left.

45:08.247 --> 45:09.373
It's where the ruins are.

45:12.251 --> 45:13.085
Okay. Here.

45:18.174 --> 45:19.258
Yeah, but we're going left.

45:19.300 --> 45:20.176
[speaking Arabic]

45:21.093 --> 45:22.386
[in English] That way is closed.

45:23.512 --> 45:25.973
Up ahead is better.

45:26.015 --> 45:27.725
I understand,           
   but the ruins are to the left.

45:27.767 --> 45:29.226
Let's take the left.

45:29.268 --> 45:31.395
Yeah, I know,           
        but we take this way.

45:58.923 --> 46:00.674
[camera shutter clicking]

46:04.637 --> 46:05.471
Mister.

46:06.722 --> 46:07.598
Mister.

46:08.808 --> 46:10.351
Please. Not...

46:10.392 --> 46:11.560
I don't want problems.

46:26.033 --> 46:27.910
Mister! Mister, please.

46:28.911 --> 46:29.787
Mister.

46:31.956 --> 46:33.124
Please, back to the car.

46:34.166 --> 46:35.126
[Chet] Yeah, yeah.

46:36.502 --> 46:38.838
[driver] Mister, please.      
           Please, mister.

46:40.339 --> 46:41.799
Please, back to the car.

46:53.519 --> 46:55.563
[indistinct chatter]

47:05.072 --> 47:06.157
[man speaking Arabic]

47:08.868 --> 47:09.743
[Imad speaking]

47:09.785 --> 47:10.828
[Asgari speaking]

47:36.228 --> 47:37.980
[Imad sighs]

48:03.130 --> 48:05.049
[in English] You can ask him    
         anything you want.

48:07.009 --> 48:10.054
About the CIA, Iran.

48:11.639 --> 48:12.640
Whatever.

48:42.670 --> 48:43.545
Thank you.

48:43.587 --> 48:45.589
[jazz music playing on speakers]

48:56.642 --> 48:58.435
I told you not to go.

48:58.477 --> 49:00.729
For fuck's sake,          
 I'm telling you Buckley's there.

49:00.771 --> 49:02.731
[Dewey] You think or you know?

49:02.773 --> 49:04.566
Give me a Delta Force team,    
      and I'll prove it to you.

49:07.987 --> 49:09.363
[Dewey] Come on.

49:09.405 --> 49:11.657
[Steve] Chet... [clears throat] 
        we all love Buckley.

49:11.699 --> 49:13.742
But you're too involved in this. 
      We need you to step back.

49:14.410 --> 49:16.412
We. Okay. Who's "we"?

49:16.453 --> 49:17.955
[Dewey]              
      Counter-Terrorism Center.

49:17.997 --> 49:18.872
CTC.

49:18.914 --> 49:20.416
It's a new division.

49:20.457 --> 49:25.129
Steve works for me now,      
   and our focus is Islamic Jihad.

49:25.170 --> 49:26.797
-It's not Iran.          
         -They're the same.

49:27.840 --> 49:29.800
Do you understand that?      
             Same thing.

49:29.842 --> 49:32.177
Asgari and Pur,          
         Syrian ambassador,

49:32.219 --> 49:33.178
setting up something new,

49:33.220 --> 49:34.513
tip of the spear          
         of the revolution.

49:34.555 --> 49:35.514
This is money, banks,

49:35.556 --> 49:37.099
direct support           
         for the operation.

49:37.141 --> 49:39.184
I think these guys may have even 
 interrogated Buckley themselves.

49:39.226 --> 49:41.103
Stop, Chet. Stop it.

49:41.145 --> 49:42.813
You yourself            
        have been telling me

49:42.855 --> 49:45.774
this is all Imad Mughniyeh,    
            this Radwan.

49:45.816 --> 49:46.900
Yeah, it is.

49:46.942 --> 49:48.235
But he's working          
       for these guys somehow.

49:48.277 --> 49:49.528
It's an Iranian op.

49:49.570 --> 49:52.156
[Dewey] Jesus Christ.       
      Iran is not your concern.

49:52.197 --> 49:53.782
What is your concern is Lebanon.

49:53.824 --> 49:56.660
And you can start by telling me 
     about the mosque in Beirut.

49:56.702 --> 49:58.996
What's the name of the, uh...   
              the Imam?

49:59.038 --> 50:01.498
Fadlallah. Sayed Muhamad      
         Hussein Fadlallah.

50:01.540 --> 50:03.500
No, Fadlallah is not Iran.     
          It's complicated.

50:03.542 --> 50:05.878
This is a Counter-Terrorism    
             matter now.

50:07.504 --> 50:08.547
Jesus Christ!

50:09.298 --> 50:10.424
It's the CTC.

50:12.343 --> 50:14.386
Maybe it's not the best division 
         for you after all.

50:16.305 --> 50:17.765
But enjoy Cyprus.

50:20.184 --> 50:21.185
Sorry, brother.

50:34.031 --> 50:35.407
[speaking Arabic]

50:50.881 --> 50:52.049
[baby cooing]

51:04.937 --> 51:06.230
-[kisses baby]           
            -[baby coos]

51:13.278 --> 51:14.113
[Imad speaking]

51:23.956 --> 51:24.790
[chuckles]

51:27.209 --> 51:29.253
dark music

51:53.110 --> 51:54.069
[in English] Thank you.

51:58.991 --> 51:59.908
Where is everyone?

52:00.868 --> 52:02.077
With Dewey, I think.

52:03.620 --> 52:04.997
Dewey is here in Beirut?

52:06.457 --> 52:07.416
[Topher] I'm sorry.

52:32.024 --> 52:34.318
[speaking Arabic]

52:40.115 --> 52:41.492
[Steve, in English]        
         We are in position.

52:47.748 --> 52:49.666
[horns blaring]

52:52.336 --> 52:53.962
[horn honking]

53:02.012 --> 53:03.347
[Chet speaking Arabic]

53:18.737 --> 53:19.905
[horn honking]

53:21.907 --> 53:23.784
[in English] Yeah, Chet Riley,   
           Beirut Station.

53:23.825 --> 53:25.118
I need the Director on the line.

53:25.994 --> 53:28.205
[telephone ringing]

53:31.083 --> 53:32.459
[man]   I have            
       Field Officer Chet Riley

53:32.501 --> 53:33.544
on the line for you, sir.

53:33.585 --> 53:35.003
[sighs]

53:35.045 --> 53:39.883
Case Officer, you're really    
     not supposed to call here.

53:39.925 --> 53:43.387
Sir, this cannot happen.

53:43.428 --> 53:44.721
We cannot have this happen.

53:44.763 --> 53:46.890
It's gonna backfire on Buckley, 
            on all of us.

53:51.478 --> 53:52.896
[hangs up receiver]

53:59.278 --> 54:00.571
[Fadlallah speaking Arabic]

54:05.117 --> 54:06.285
[Fadlallah speaking]

54:29.766 --> 54:31.768
[indistinct chatter]

54:35.731 --> 54:37.608
-[in English] It's him.      
            -[Dewey] Mm.

54:37.649 --> 54:38.692
[Steve] Thirty seconds.

54:39.568 --> 54:40.861
Uh, let's proceed.

54:42.946 --> 54:44.323
[man speaking Arabic]

54:46.658 --> 54:48.952
tense music

55:00.547 --> 55:01.340
[explosion]

55:11.933 --> 55:13.185
[in English] It's time to go.

55:20.567 --> 55:22.569
[people shouting and sobbing]

55:22.611 --> 55:23.487
[coughs]

55:29.534 --> 55:31.495
[indistinct chatter]

55:38.335 --> 55:40.837
[Imad grunts, coughs]

55:44.800 --> 55:46.843
[woman shouting in Arabic]

55:51.556 --> 55:52.683
[coughing]

55:58.730 --> 55:59.690
[Imad] Haidar!

56:04.152 --> 56:05.195
Haidar!

56:20.544 --> 56:21.837
Haidar!

56:25.215 --> 56:26.508
Haidar!

56:26.550 --> 56:28.552
somber music

57:41.958 --> 57:43.960
pensive music
